{"downloaded": true, "htmlmade": false, "id": "34744514", "source": "MED", "pmid": "34744514", "pmcid": "PMC8567742", "fullTextIdList": {"fullTextId": "PMC8567742"}, "doi": "10.1080/14747731.2021.1979717", "title": "The global climate of land politics.", "authorString": "Franco JC, Borras SM.", "authorList": {"author": [{"fullName": "Franco JC", "firstName": "Jennifer C", "lastName": "Franco", "initials": "JC", "authorAffiliationDetailsList": {"authorAffiliation": {"affiliation": "Transnational Institute (TNI), Amsterdam, Netherlands."}}}, {"fullName": "Borras SM Jr", "firstName": "Saturnino M", "lastName": "Borras", "initials": "SM", "authorAffiliationDetailsList": {"authorAffiliation": {"affiliation": "International Institute of Social Studies (ISS) of Erasmus University Rotterdam, The Hague, Netherlands."}}}]}, "dataLinksTagsList": {"dataLinkstag": "altmetrics"}, "journalInfo": {"issue": "7", "volume": "18", "journalIssueId": "3265984", "dateOfPublication": "2021", "monthOfPublication": "0", "yearOfPublication": "2021", "printPublicationDate": "2021-01-01", "journal": {"title": "Globalizations", "ISOAbbreviation": "Globalizations", "medlineAbbreviation": "Globalizations", "NLMid": "101630252", "ISSN": "1474-7731", "ESSN": "1474-774X"}}, "pubYear": "2021", "pageInfo": "1277-1297", "abstractText": "Land is a key input in economic production and production-waste sink. This links land to the causes of and responses to climate change. The dominant climate action ideas are based on the concept of 'land tenure security' which, in a global context marked by land-based inequities, means ratifying what already exists. This reinforces undemocratic social structures and institutions that themselves contribute to climate change. A restructuring of global land politics is called for, without which any analyses of and responses to climate change are at best superficial, and at worst, flawed and self-defeating. What is needed is to acknowledge the pervasive land-based social inequities in the world, and to end such inequities by pursuing a redistribution of a range of access to a range of land and resources in ways that categorically benefit the working people.", "affiliation": "Transnational Institute (TNI), Amsterdam, Netherlands.", "publicationStatus": "epublish", "language": "eng", "pubModel": "Electronic-eCollection", "pubTypeList": {"pubType": ["research-article", "Journal Article"]}, "grantsList": {"grant": {"agency": "European Research Council", "acronym": "ERC_", "orderIn": "0"}}, "keywordList": {"keyword": ["Ipcc", "Land Tenure Security", "Redistributive Land Policy", "Climate Change Politics", "Land Politics"]}, "fullTextUrlList": {"fullTextUrl": [{"availability": "Subscription required", "availabilityCode": "S", "documentStyle": "doi", "site": "DOI", "url": "https://doi.org/10.1080/14747731.2021.1979717"}, {"availability": "Open access", "availabilityCode": "OA", "documentStyle": "html", "site": "Europe_PMC", "url": "https://europepmc.org/articles/PMC8567742"}, {"availability": "Open access", "availabilityCode": "OA", "documentStyle": "pdf", "site": "Europe_PMC", "url": "https://europepmc.org/articles/PMC8567742?pdf=render"}]}, "isOpenAccess": "Y", "inEPMC": "Y", "inPMC": "N", "hasPDF": "Y", "hasBook": "N", "hasSuppl": "N", "citedByCount": "0", "hasData": "N", "hasReferences": "Y", "hasTextMinedTerms": "N", "hasDbCrossReferences": "N", "hasLabsLinks": "Y", "license": "cc by-nc-nd", "authMan": "N", "epmcAuthMan": "N", "nihAuthMan": "N", "hasTMAccessionNumbers": "N", "dateOfCreation": "2021-11-08", "firstIndexDate": "2021-11-27", "fullTextReceivedDate": "2021-11-06", "dateOfRevision": "2021-11-10", "electronicPublicationDate": "2021-09-30", "firstPublicationDate": "2021-09-30"}